summary: LETTER FROM KENT A. LISKO  (CA) OPPOSSING PROVISIONS OF EARLY WARNING REPORTING (EWR) REGULATION THAT REQUIRE MANUFACTURERS  THAT PRODUCE OVER 500 SMALL TO MEDIUM TRAILERS(THOSE WITH A GROSS VEHICLE WEIGHT (GVWR) OFF LESS THAN 26000 POUNDS) TO SUBMIT COMPREHENSIVE EARLY WARNING REPORTS TO NHTSA. MR LISKO THINKS THAT SUCH REPORTS WOULD PUT HIM AND HIS COLLEAGUES OUT OF BUSINESS.  *AK
